\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 5. L. pulverulenta} (Lag.) Heywood, {\i op. cit.} 184 (1975) ({\i Pyrethrum hispanicum} var.{\i  pinnatifidum} Willk. pro parte, {\i P. pulverulentum} Lag., {\i Tanacetum pulverulentum} (Lag.) Schultz Bip.). Greyish- to whitish-tomentose. Stems 10-20 cm, numerous, crowded, erect or ascending. Basal and lower cauline leaves oblong-linear, pinnatifid with 7-15 approximate, linear, mucronate lobes. Outer involucral bracts ovate, acute, tomentose, with a narrow, dark membranous margin. Capitula 1·5-2·5 cm in diameter. Ligules white, yellowish towards the base. Achenes with 7-10 ribs. Pappus a corona. •{\i  Spain and Portugal.} Hs Lu.
