\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. P. pectinata} (L.) Boiss., {\i Voy. Bot. Midi Esp.}{\b  2}: 320 (1840). Stems 10-25(-30) cm, usually hairy. Leaves pectinate-pinnatifid, the lobes acute to acuminate, appressed-hairy. Capitula 2-2·5 cm in diameter. Ligules 5-6·5 mm, yellow. Pappus an auricle 1·5-2 mm at anthesis. Achene 2-2·5 mm.{\i  Sandy places and cultivated fields. • C. & S. Spain.} Hs.
