\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. L. repandum} (L.) DC., {\i Prodr.}{\b  6}: 19 (1838). Stems 20-50 cm, simple or branched above, glabrous. Basal leaves 2-6 × 1-2 cm, spathulate to oblong-spathulate, obtuse, serrate, long-petiolate; middle and upper cauline leaves sessile. Capitula 20-40 mm in diameter. Ligules 6-12 mm, yellow. 2n = 18. •{\i  Portugal, S.W. & N.W. Spain.} Hs Lu.
